{{confused|Amharic}} {{Infobox language |name= Amara |region=parts of [[West New Britain|West New Britain Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]] |speakers=230 |date=2011 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[North New Guinea languages|North New Guinea]] |fam6=[[Ngero–Vitiaz languages|Ngero–Vitiaz]] |fam7=Vitiaz |iso3=aie |glotto=amar1272 |glottorefname=Amara }}
'''NAmara''' is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] spoken by about 1200 individuals along the northwest coast of [[West New Britain|West New Britain Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]] on the island of [[New Britain]]. Speakers have close to a 100% bilingualism with [[Bariai language|Bariai]], and many also speak [[Tok Pisin]].
