{{Infobox language |name=Miisiirii |altname= |states=[[Sudan]] |region=[[West Darfur]] |ethnicity=[[Messiria tribe|Messiria]] |speakers=? |date= |ref = |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Eastern Sudanic languages|Eastern Sudanic]]? |fam3=[[Astaboran languages|Astaboran]]? |fam4=[[Taman languages|Taman]] |iso3=none |iso3comment=(counted as {{ethnolink|tma}}) |glotto=miis1236 |glottorefname=Miisiirii }}
'''Miisiirii''' is a language of western [[Sudan]], spoken by the [[Messiria tribe|Messiria]] of [[Jebel Mun]] (Jebel Moon) in Darfur. It belongs to the [[Taman languages|Taman]] language family. It is often considered a dialect of [[Tama language|Tama]], though it is not particularly close.
