The '''Si La''' (also '''Sila''' or '''Syla''') are an [[ethnic group]] of about 1,800 people living in northern [[Laos]] and another 600 living in [[Lai Châu Province]], [[Northwest (Vietnam)|Northwest]] region, [[Vietnam]].

== Culture ==
The Si La people speak a [[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman language]] closely related to [[Hani language|Hani]] (Edmondson 2002). Their primary occupation is the cultivation of [[cereal]]s, augmented by [[hunting]] and [[foraging]]. One of the most distinctive Si La customs is [[tooth painting]]: men traditionally painted their teeth red, while women painted theirs black. The custom is increasingly uncommon among the younger generation.

